text.tspan: Induction NOT required
Please set the Roomba off to clean the floor if it looks dirty,
or return the Roomba to its dock for charging if it gets stuck.
Empty
Please empty the Roomba occasionally!
Press down on the circle highlighted in
green and slide the waste bin out.
Empty it in the bin.
Put it back.
Clean
Press clean button to make the Roomba
perform a general hoovering of the
floor. It will attempt to clean whereever
it can get to and return to it's dock
when done.
Spot
Move the Roomba to where you want it
to clean and press the spot button, it
will circle in the vicinity and stop after a
short while.
Return Roomba to dock when done.
Dock
Press dock to make the Roomba return
to it's dock for charging. If it struggles to
find the dock, pick it up, put it down just
in front of the dock and press dock. (or
just put it back on the dock manually)

flowRoot.flowPara: A: Pick it up (it will stop) and put it back on it's dock
Q: Will it drive down the stairs?
A: No, it has cliff sensors
Q: Nothing happens when I press the buttons!
A: It probably needs charing, put it back on its dock so the metal contacts underneath touch the base and the LED lights up to indicate charging.
